description:
&lt;p&gt;We have recently been awarded a 10 year contract for Adult Community Health Services across Bristol, North Somerset &amp; South Gloucestershire (BNSSG) which is a really exciting opportunity for us in Sirona care &amp; health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The growth and development of Sirona is a new and exciting chapter. This will enable us, together with our colleagues across the system, to work with individuals, carers and families to transform out-of-hospital services to support people to live longer and healthier lives, accessing care and support close to where they live and ensure consistency and equity across BNSSG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working towards setting up Integrated Network Teams (INT) aligned to Primary care networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be 18 INTs across BNSSG. These teams will be fully integrated ‘out of hospital’ health care services, delivered in close collaboration with primary and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These teams will support and empower people to stay and age well, reduce the demand for emergency hospital services and long term care placements. Integrated multidisciplinary teams, offer both planned and unplanned interventions to improve outcomes for service users and support more people to self-care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each INT will be made up of the following;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Matrons/Advanced Care Practitioners - Long term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered nursing &amp; therapy professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled support staff including nurse associates, assistant practitioners and support workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Public health nursing (Active Ageing service)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated administrators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated network teams will offer a consistent service from 8am to 8pm, 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you clapped for us in April then we want you to come join us and help support our community, these are all new posts due to extra funding as the fight continues over winter…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about delivering exceptional community-based therapy, allowing service users to improve their quality of life and optimise their function? Are you committed to a Home First ethos, where people can rehabilitate and recover in their own environment, optimising their physical and emotional wellbeing?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sirona Community Rehabilitation Teams (CRT) are an innovative and dynamic service. We aim to assist in preventing hospital admission and to facilitate timely hospital discharge (Discharge to Assess). We also provide Planned (Domiciliary) therapy to ensure that patients are assessed and supported early in the journey to maintain their optimal level of independence and hence avoid longer term concerns. We provide active rehabilitation to patients in their place of residence to maximise their functional potential and support them to remain independent within their homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated physiotherapist to join our busy and dynamic team. We are looking for a physiotherapist with experience of community working, to promote independence and choice for our service users and their carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we will give you the opportunity to develop specialist community skills and enhance your multidisciplinary working; we will provide you with regular training and supervision opportunities as well as the opportunity to develop your leadership skills in supervising Rehab Support Workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working within a friendly and supportive multidisciplinary team alongside other Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, Speech and Language Therapists, Rehabilitation Support Workers and Physiotherapy Technicians. We collaborate closely with our Community Nursing colleagues and other Acute, Community and Social Care partners. We offer a flexible service which covers extended hours operating 7 days a week, to support our service user needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have full and part time hours available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the job description attached and please get in touch if you ahve further questions : Jayrah - sirona.recruitment@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
